


'/pronouns.mp4'),
(1, 'Present Tense (Indicative)', 'Everyday Verbs in Action', 'Use regular and irregular verbs in the present tense to describe routines and actions: Learn how to conjugate and use verbs in the present tense to describe daily routines and actions. With examples like “Yo estudio español” and “Nosotros comemos juntos”, students will gain confidence using regular and irregular verbs. Activity: Fill in the blanks with the correct form of the verb in the present tense.','present_tense.mp4'),
(1, 'Days of the Week and Months of the Year in Spanish', 'Living by the Spanish Calendar', 'Use days, months, and dates in conversation: Discover how to talk about time in Spanish—days, months, and important dates. Students will create a personal calendar in Spanish and practice using expressions such as “Hoy es lunes” and “Mi cumpleaños es en julio”. Activity: Select the correct day or month that matches each sentence.', 'calendar.mp4'),
(1, 'Asking for Help in Spanish', 'Communicate with Confidence', 'Use essential expressions to ask for help and clarification in real situations: Learn essential expressions to ask for help and clarification, such as “¿Puedes ayudarme?” or “No entiendo.” Through situational dialogues, students will gain the confidence to handle real-life interactions in Spanish-speaking environments. Activity: Choose the best phrase to ask for help in each situation.', 'help.mp4'),
(1, 'Interrogative and Exclamatory Pronouns', 'Asking and Expressing with Emotion', 'Form and use questions and exclamations to express curiosity and emotion: Explore how to use question words (qué, cómo, cuándo, dónde, por qué) and exclamatory expressions (¡Qué bonito! ¡Cómo me gusta!) to add curiosity and emotion to your communication. Students will create and answer their own questions in pairs. Activity: Complete each question using the correct interrogative word (qué, cómo, cuándo, dónde, por qué).', 'interrogativos.mp4'),
(1, 'Personality Traits and Character', 'Describing Yourself and Others',
'Learn vocabulary to describe personality, character, and emotions: Learn vocabulary to describe personality and character traits, from simpático to trabajador. Through interviews, matching games, and creative writing, students will express who they are and understand others in Spanish.
Activity: Match each adjective with its English meaning and write two words that describe your personality.',
'personality.mp4');